	      <h4 id = "week4">Week 8</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b> At week 8 the embryo shapes  more and more like a human. The brain is very important so  the head size is about half of the entire body length. The little face continues to show features. Nose a top lip appears, and there is a little tongue and taste buds in the mouth now. The inner and outer ear form. The eyes are located on the sides of the head, covered by rudimentary eyelids. </p>
			<p>The fetal heart is now similar to an adult heart, complete with all four chambers: two atria and two ventricles. It’s doing its job, pumping blood. Meanwhile, the baby has completely transitioned to getting its nutrition from mom, receiving everything it needs through the umbilical cord. </p>
			<p>Bones and cartilage keep developing, with some cartilage beginning to harden. There are discernible joints in the growing arms, with the forearms and upper arms clearly distinguished. The stomach has descended from the chest to the abdomen and begun to produce stomach acid. In addition to the stomach, the esophagus and various portions of the intestines can be discerned in the digestive system.</p>
			<p>The nervous system,  by the end of week 8, the brain and spinal column divide up their responsibilities and begin performing their respective functions.</p>
			<p>Boys are developing testicles and girls are developing ovaries, but you can’t tell the baby’s sex on an ultrasound yet and it's illegal in India.</p>

			<p><b>Mom : </b> In week 8, Your growing belly is not obvious, but you might feel belly enlarge and difficulty button your old jeans. Avoid Close-fitting clothing as it become uncomfortable. Your breasts have grown, your nipples get darker and swell slightly, and veins may become more visible. Make sure to switch to a comfortable, looser bra. Remember that clothing that is comfortable and pleasant to the touch is very important in pregnancy and may help you feel better about yourself. </p>
			<p>The hormonal swings are still with you, bringing along rapid fatigue, sleepiness, and irritability. Different people find their skin and hair may react differently to hormones. </p>
			<p>The volume of blood circulating in your body increases, which can sometimes cause varicose veins in lower limb. You ma feel swelling or heaviness in the legs, especially in the evening, star-shaped clusters of blood vessels, or clearly visible veins. Whether this is your first time experiencing varicose veins or if it’s an existing condition exacerbated by pregnancy, ask your doctor if you should see a specialist.</p>

			<p><b>Useful tips</b></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Still you didn't contacted your doctor please go to your doctor and do</li>
				<li>routine check up, </li>
				<li>ultrasound and </li>
				<li>basic blood reports (hemoglobin level thyroid hormones problem , blood sugar.)</li>
			</ul>

			<p>If you not started prenatal vitamins please start it.</p>
			<p>After 8 weeks of pregnancy few womens have peak in nausea and vomiting indigestion, anorexia don't worry  about it  and u can take supportive,  symptomatic and safe medicine prescribed by your doctor</p>
			<p>Some women may have weight losses up to 3 kg.sex during pregnancy is safe if you and your partner mentally and physically comfortable.You can  do your daily physical routine activity with exercise that are safe in pregnancy.You may have craving for non nutritious unhealthy food but be aware of it and avoid it.Drink lots of water to stay hydrated.</p>
			<p>Wash fruits and vegetables thoroughly, and peel them if required, to avoid accidental consumption of pesticides.Eat small quantities throughout the day as it helps you digest food quickly and aids in feeding your growing baby properly.Do not take any pain killers or antibiotics without consulting your physician.</p>
			<p>Try not to stress yourself out. Enroll yourself in yoga or meditation classes.Do not wear tight fitting clothes that restrict breathing space for the body.Avoid long-distance travel as it puts unnecessary pressure on the body.Do not lift heavy weights as they put pressure on the growing baby.</p>
